21 was provided; and (3) the total percentage of staff members that attended such training during
22 the immediately preceding school year. Section 1.5 additionally authorizes the Department of
23 Education to coordinate with each regional training program or engage with an appropriate
24 vendor for the professional development of teachers and administrators to develop curricula
25 for such training that the board of trustees of a school district may use to satisfy the
26 requirements of section 1.5. Section 2 of this bill makes a conforming change to apply the
27 existing definition of “professional development training” to the provisions of section 1.5.
28 Section 2.3 of this bill requires the Department of Education to develop and maintain a
29 system to assist the board of trustees of a school district and the governing body of a charter
30 school or university school for profoundly gifted pupils in addressing disproportionate or high
31 levels of pupil discipline. Section 2.3 of this bill requires a school district or governing body
32 that is required to participate in the system to take certain actions to ensure the proper
33 implementation and effectiveness of the system. Section 2.3 of this bill requires the
34 Department to submit an annual report to the Legislature or the Joint Interim Standing
35 Committee on Education concerning the implementation of and outcomes from the system.
36 Section 2.7 of this bill applies certain definitions in existing law to section 2.3.
